    "body": "It's a questionable feature rather than a bug. Magics use curly braces as Python formatting syntax, so that you can use Python variables in magic commands:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nx = '--foo' if a else '--bar'\r\n%run script.py {x}\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can escape the braces by doubling them, i.e. `{{100}}`.\r\n\r\nSee #5978 for more discussion about this."
